These tests check the Gwibber application and its integration to Twitter, Facebook and Flickr.
<dl>
        Test-Case Name: gwibber/gwb-001
        Test how gwibber launches if no online accounts are setup

	<dt>Open Gwibber Social Client</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber window will appear</dd>
		<dd>If no online accounts have been setup, the online accounts window from system settings should appear.</dd>
		<dd>Online Accounts window should display a list of available online services, those available for integration with Gwibber include: Facebook, Flickr, Twitter and identi.ca </dd>
</dl>

        Test-Case Name: gwibber/gwb-002
        Test twitter integration

<dl>
	<dt>Create a Twitter account</dt>
		<ul>
			<dt>Introduce the credentials (username and password)</dt>
			<dt>Accept permissions</dt>
			<dt>When asked, introduce the password of your ubuntu user to access the keyring</dt>
		</ul>
	</dt>
        <dt>Close Online Accounts Window</dt>

	<dt>Open Gwibber</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display Twitter’s timeline on the home screen or when you click on the 'Home' button</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Messages" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of twitter messages when you click on the 'Messages' button.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Reply" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of @reply twitter messages when you click on the 'Reply' button.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Private Messages" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of private twitter messages when you click on the 'Private Messages' button.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Attachments" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of any tweets containing images, links or videos from the Twitter's timeline when you click the "Attachments" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Searches" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a search box to allow you to search for mentioned terms or topics in Twitter's timeline when you click the "Searches" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Users" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of people you follow on Twitter when you click the "Users" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on a user's picture or user's name on Twitter's timeline</dt>
            <dd>Gwibber should open a link to the user's post on the default browser.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "New Messsage" button</dt>
                <dd>A popup should appear below with a textfield.</dd>
                <dd>A tiny twitter icon should appear below the textfield to show that any update you post here will be posted on twitter.</dd>
 		<dd>A tiny "character counter" should appear below the textfield showing the amount of characters you have left. 140 characters is the maximum for twitter. </dd>
                <dd>A send button should appear below the textfield</dd>
        <dt>Click on send with content in the textfield</td>
                <dd>Gwibber should post the update to twitter so long as the twitter icon below the textfield is active</dd>
        <dt>Click on send with content in the textfield and the twitter icon below the textfield is inactive</td>
                <dd>Gwibber should not post the update to twitter</dd>

	<dt>Open Online Accounts by selecting "Accounts" from Gwibber's "Edit" menu</dt>
            <dd>Online Accounts window will be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Remove all existing accounts</dt>
            <dd>Gwibber should not display any "new" feeds from a deleted account. Old feeds are however still present.</dd>
</dl>

        Test-Case Name: gwibber/gwb-003
        Test facebook integration

<dl>
	<dt>Create a Facebook account
		<ul>
			<dt>Introduce the credentials (username and password)</dt>
			<dt>Accept permissions</dt>
			<dt>When asked, introduce the password of your ubuntu user to access the keyring</dt>
		</ul>
	</dt>
	<dt>Close Online Accounts Window</dt>

	<dt>Open Gwibber</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display Facebook’s timeline on the home screen or when you click on the 'Home' button</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Messages" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of Facebook messages when you click on the 'Messages' button.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Reply" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of private Facebook messages when you click on the 'Private Messages' button.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Attachments" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of any Facebook updates containing images, links or videos from the Facebook's timeline when you click the "Attachments" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Searches" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a search box to allow you to search for mentioned terms or topics in Facebook's timeline when you click the "Searches" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on the "Users" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of people you are friends with on Facebook when you click the "Users" button. </dd>
        <dt>Click on a user's picture or user's name on Facebook's timeline</dt>
            <dd>Gwibber should open a link to the user's post on the default browser.</dd>
        <dt>Click on the "New Messsage" button</dt>
                <dd>A popup should appear below with a textfield.</dd>
                <dd>A tiny Facebook icon should appear below the textfield to show that any update you post here will be posted on Facebook.</dd>
 		<dd>A tiny "character counter" should appear below the textfield showing the amount of characters you have left. 140 characters is the maximum</dd>
                <dd>A send button should appear below the textfield</dd>
        <dt>Click on send with content in the textfield</td>
                <dd>Gwibber should post the update to Facebook so long as the Facebook icon below the textfield is active</dd>
        <dt>Click on send with content in the textfield and the Facebook icon below the textfield is inactive</td>
                <dd>Gwibber should not post the update to Facebook</dd>

	<dt>Open Online Accounts by selecting "Accounts" from Gwibber's "Edit" menu</dt>
            <dd>Online Accounts window will be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Remove all existing accounts</dt>
            <dd>Gwibber should not display any "new" feeds from a deleted account. </dd>
</dl>

        Test-Case Name: gwibber/gwb-004
        Test flicker integration

<dl>
	<dt>Create a Flickr account
		<ul>
			<dt>Introduce the credentials (username and password)</dt>
			<dt>Accept permissions</dt>
			<dt>When asked, introduce the password of your ubuntu user to access the keyring</dt>
		</ul>
	</dt>

	<dt>Close Online Accounts Window</dt>

	<dt>Open Gwibber</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display Flickr’s timeline on the home screen or when you click on the 'Home' button</dd>
       <dt>Click on the "Attachments" button</dt>
		<dd>Gwibber should display a list of any Flickr's updates containing images from the Flickr's timeline when you click the "Attachments" button. </dd>
         <dt>Click on the "New Messsage" button</dt>
                <dd> A popup should appear below with a textfield. Updates cannot however be sent to Flickr since flickr it is not that type of service.</dd>
</dl>
         Test-Case Name: gwibber/gwb-005
        Test gwibber feed after deleting all online accounts.
<dl>
	<dt>Open Online Accounts by selecting "Accounts" from Gwibber's "Edit" menu</dt>
            <dd>Online Accounts window will be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Remove all existing accounts</dt>
            <dd>Gwibber should not display any "new" feeds from a deleted account. </dd>
</dl>

<strong>If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'failed' result and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result.</strong>
